OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Fri 12 Jun to Sun 21 Jun
OL,6,FProbably remaining fairly unsettled
OL,7,Fearly in this period with Atlantic low
OL,8,Fpressure systems passing to the north
OL,9,Fand west of the UK. These will bring
OL,10,Fshowers or longer spells of rain at
OL,11,Ftimes. The wettest conditions will be
OL,12,Fin the northwest, with more in the way
OL,13,Fof drier interludes in the southeast.
OL,14,FStrong winds may affect parts of the
OL,15,FUK at times, especially the northwest.
OL,16,FHigher pressure and more settled
OL,17,Fconditions will likely become more
OL,18,Festablished through the period,
OL,19,Finitially in the east or southeast,
OL,20,Fbut perhaps becoming more widespread.
OL,21,FThere will probably still be some
OL,22,Fshowers or longer spells of rain at
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Ftimes though. Temperatures are likely
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fto be near or a little above normal
OL,25,Foverall.
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
SC,0003
CT,20,T
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F163A1780837873
OL,1,Wj5hw1~{4k7juhw1{$             G3/3
OL,2,W+.-'"-$/*%*%*%/"-$/*%Q,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 22 Jun to Mon 6 Jul
OL,6,FMuch of the period may be relatively
OL,7,Fsettled for most of the UK. High
OL,8,Fpressure is likely to be in the
OL,9,Fvicinity of the UK bringing drier than
OL,10,Faverage conditions, especially to the
OL,11,Fsouth. There will still probably be
OL,12,Fsome showers or longer spells of rain
OL,13,Fat times though, particularly in the
OL,14,Fnorth. Winds will mostly be fairly
OL,15,Flight, although spells of strong winds
OL,16,Fare possible at times in the north.
OL,17,FTemperatures will probably be a little
OL,18,Fabove normal and it could be very warm
OL,19,For hot at times in the south.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
